{"name":"Wrestling","permission":{"default":0,"fvu77M1xxrZr85ZK":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>You are an expert grappler. You can make unarmed attacks with a +10% bonus to Weapon Skill when attempting to grapple. Furthermore, you gain a +10% bonus on grappling Strength Tests.</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"bonus":{"value":null,"display":" You can make unarmed attacks with a +10% bonus to Weapon Skill when attempting to grapple. Furthermore, you gain a +10% bonus on grappling Strength Tests.","target":"","constant":false},"relatedSkills":[""]},"flags":{},"img":"systems/wfrp2e/icons/blank.png","_id":"QEpEI8iT25TrgAJq"}
{"_id":"hfSOXh5gQv2FHZcf","name":" Divine Lore (Ulric)","permission":{"default":0,"fvu77M1xxrZr85ZK":3},"type":"talent","data":{"description":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":"<p>Your dedication to your deity is such that your prayers can produce magical effects. Divine Lore is unusual in that it is not one talent, but many different ones. Such is the devotion required that you can only ever know one Divine Lore. Each Divine Lore talent is a separate magical proficiency, with the specialty noted in parenthesis. For example, Divine Lore (Sigmar) is a different talent than Divine Lore (Ulric). If you know a Divine Lore, you can attempt to cast any spell from that lore.&nbsp;</p>"},"gmdescription":{"type":"String","label":"Description","value":""},"bonus":{"value":null,"display":"If you know a Divine Lore, you can attempt to cast any spell from that lore.","target":"","constant":false},"relatedSkills":[""]},"flags":{},"img":"systems/wfrp2e/icons/blank.png"}
